space.arim.api.util.collect

Interface InfinitySet<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the element type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<E>, CollectionEmptyHelper<E>, Iterable<E>, Set<E>, SetEmptyHelper<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    UnmodifiableInfinitySet<E>

    public interface InfinitySet<E>
extends SetEmptyHelper<E>
    Represents a set which contains all possible elements.
    Use create() for instantiation.

    Principles:
    * All elements are contained within infinity.
    1 Because infinity cannot be quantified, attempts to select individual elements will always fail.
    2 Because infinity, when added to, remains infinity, attempts to add elements always indicate an unchanged set.
    3 Infinity cannot be reduced in number or size. Subtraction has no effect.

    The specifications follow from the principles.
    Specifications:
    * size() == Integer.MAX_VALUE, isEmpty() is always false. (principle 1)
    * contains(Object) and containsAll(Collection) always return true. (principle 1)
    * SetEmptyHelper.iterator() returns an empty iterator. (principle 2)
    * SetEmptyHelper.toArray() and SetEmptyHelper.toArray(Object[]) return empty arrays. (principle 2)
    * add(Object) and addAll(Collection) always return false. (principle 3)
    * remove(Object), removeAll(Collection), and retainAll(Collection) always return true. (principles 1 and 4)
    * clear() does nothing. (principle 4)
    Author:
    A248
